      <p class="govuk-body">To better support you, we've provided information on the various roles and responsibilities within the criminal justice system.</p>

      <h2 class="govuk-heading-m" id="police-officers">Court Ushers</h2>
      <p class="govuk-body">They prepare the court room and ensure that witnesses, defendants, and lawyers are present.</p>

      <h2 class="govuk-heading-m" id="crown-prosecution-service-prosecutors">Crown Prosecution Service (CPS) Prosecutors</h2>
      <p class="govuk-body">They decide whether to bring cases to court and prosecute criminal cases on behalf of the state.</p>

      <h2 class="govuk-heading-m" id="crown-prosecution-service-prosecutors">Defence Solicitors and Barristers</h2>
      <p class="govuk-body">They represent the accused, ensuring their legal rights are protected and providing a defence in court.</p>

      <h2 class="govuk-heading-m" id="crown-prosecution-service-prosecutors">Judges and Magistrates</h2>
      <p class="govuk-body">They oversee court proceedings, make rulings on legal matters, and ensure trials are conducted fairly.</p>

      <h2 class="govuk-heading-m" id="crown-prosecution-service-prosecutors">Legal Advisers</h2>
      <p class="govuk-body">A lawyer who advises magistrates and guides proceedings.</p>

      <h2 class="govuk-heading-m" id="crown-prosecution-service-prosecutors">Police Officers</h2>
      <p class="govuk-body">They investigate crimes, make arrests, and ensure public safety. The officer in charge is responsible for overseeing the case.</p>

      <h2 class="govuk-heading-m" id="crown-prosecution-service-prosecutors">Police Witness Care Officers</h2>
      <p class="govuk-body">They provide key updates about the progress of the case after somebody is charged through to a court outcome.</p>

      <h2 class="govuk-heading-m" id="crown-prosecution-service-prosecutors">Probation Officers</h2>
      <p class="govuk-body">They supervise offenders in the community, helping them reintegrate into society while ensuring they comply with the terms of their release.</p>

      <h2 class="govuk-heading-m" id="crown-prosecution-service-prosecutors">Victim Caseworkers, Advocates, and Support Workers</h2>
      <p class="govuk-body">These professionals provide support and assistance to victims of crime, helping them navigate the criminal justice process.</p>

      <h2 class="govuk-heading-m" id="crown-prosecution-service-prosecutors">Witness Service Volunteers</h2>
      <p class="govuk-body">They give practical help to someone when going to court to give evidence.</p>
